00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:57,495 --> 00:01:01,166
THE WONDERFOOLS

2
00:01:14,387 --> 00:01:16,681
THE HOLY BIBLE

3
00:01:41,206 --> 00:01:42,707
Are you managing okay in here?

4
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:47,086
I've been having a good time,
thanks to you.

5
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:51,132
I hear you carry a Bible everywhere.

6
00:01:51,216 --> 00:01:53,676
So, have you been saved?

7
00:01:55,303 --> 00:01:56,888
At their core,

8
00:01:56,971 --> 00:02:00,600
all religions are mere deceptions
devised to control humans' anxiety.

9
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:03,853
Fictitious and hypocritical words

10
00:02:03,937 --> 00:02:06,064
used to sugarcoat and glorify death.

11
00:02:07,982 --> 00:02:10,360
They're nothing but lies to incite people.

12
00:02:11,903 --> 00:02:13,071
However…

13
00:02:16,699 --> 00:02:18,284
I am the real deal.

14
00:02:20,536 --> 00:02:22,956
I really did create that child.

15
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:26,960
That child.

16
00:02:27,627 --> 00:02:28,753
Where are they now?

17
00:02:30,755 --> 00:02:32,215
What do you mean by that?

18
00:02:33,174 --> 00:02:36,511
If the Child of Eternity truly does exist,

19
00:02:36,594 --> 00:02:37,971
prove it to me.

20
00:02:41,683 --> 00:02:43,726
This will be the last chance I give you

21
00:02:44,227 --> 00:02:46,854
to get out on parole.

22
00:02:48,564 --> 00:02:49,732
"Now faith

23
00:02:50,608 --> 00:02:53,069
is confidence in what we hope for

24
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:55,989
and assurance about what we do not see."

25
00:03:00,118 --> 00:03:02,161
"All who believe in me

26
00:03:02,245 --> 00:03:04,080
shall receive salvation."

27
00:03:11,921 --> 00:03:12,755
<i>But</i>

28
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:18,219
<i>the Child of Eternity I remember</i>
<i>was definitely a boy.</i>

29
00:03:19,637 --> 00:03:20,805
<i>It's okay.</i>

30
00:03:21,431 --> 00:03:22,974
<i>I can't die.</i>

31
00:03:23,850 --> 00:03:26,185
<i>There's only one way to confirm it.</i>

32
00:03:57,842 --> 00:04:00,219
Where'd she go?
Am I the only one who can't see her?

33
00:04:00,303 --> 00:04:02,597
Where did she go all of a sudden?

34
00:04:03,181 --> 00:04:04,140
Incredible.

35
00:04:47,308 --> 00:04:48,351
Chae…

36
00:05:33,104 --> 00:05:37,191
EPISODE 3
BRUTES AND BAD LUCK DO COME IN DROVES

37
00:05:37,275 --> 00:05:38,443
<i>It was him,</i>

38
00:05:38,943 --> 00:05:39,777
<i>Number 3972.</i>

39
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:42,697
Really? Are you sure it was 3972?

40
00:05:43,781 --> 00:05:44,615
Do you know him?

41
00:05:44,699 --> 00:05:47,201
He's the kid Pal-ho used to hate.
Remember?

42
00:05:48,119 --> 00:05:49,829
When his ability first manifested,

43
00:05:49,912 --> 00:05:51,873
Father's attention shifted
entirely to him.

44
00:05:51,956 --> 00:05:53,916
That's enough.

45
00:05:56,002 --> 00:05:58,254
It does feel too eerie
to be a coincidence.

46
00:06:00,173 --> 00:06:02,508
Why is he back in Haeseong?
Didn't you ask him?

47
00:06:06,679 --> 00:06:08,347
He hurled a variant into the air.

48
00:06:09,765 --> 00:06:11,601
I think he was looking for something.

49
00:06:13,352 --> 00:06:14,687
What do you think?

50
00:06:16,564 --> 00:06:17,690
Do you think Father--

51
00:06:17,773 --> 00:06:18,941
Unlikely.

52
00:06:19,025 --> 00:06:21,527
Father wouldn't call in others
without telling us.

53
00:06:22,570 --> 00:06:23,696
Would he?

54
00:06:25,698 --> 00:06:26,949
Haven't you heard anything?

55
00:06:28,701 --> 00:06:30,495
I'll look into it,

56
00:06:31,245 --> 00:06:33,080
so you two keep your mouths shut.

57
00:06:33,581 --> 00:06:34,665
About what?

58
00:06:38,711 --> 00:06:40,880
Another variant has appeared, Father.

59
00:06:40,963 --> 00:06:43,174
Then why are you still here?
Go collect it.

60
00:06:45,593 --> 00:06:46,636
Yes, Father.

61
00:07:02,151 --> 00:07:03,778
Something's fishy.

62
00:07:21,254 --> 00:07:22,213
Are you awake?

63
00:07:23,589 --> 00:07:26,467
You sure look peaceful
when you're passed out.

64
00:07:26,551 --> 00:07:27,760
What

65
00:07:28,261 --> 00:07:29,095
is that?

66
00:07:30,012 --> 00:07:31,222
What happened?

67
00:07:31,305 --> 00:07:32,848
I swear I threw it gently.

68
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:37,019
But how on earth did the soda can
pierce a wall?

69
00:07:39,981 --> 00:07:41,190
Why am I here?

70
00:07:41,274 --> 00:07:45,570
Mr. Son left you here. He found you
passed out in the abandoned greenhouse.

71
00:08:00,001 --> 00:08:01,836
Ro-bin, I think I…

72
00:08:01,919 --> 00:08:02,878
Yeah?

73
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:07,633
It wasn't a near-death experience.

74
00:08:08,217 --> 00:08:09,510
Nor was it time travel.

75
00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:13,014
Of course it wasn't.
How could that possibly happen?

76
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:16,642
It was teleportation.

77
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:52,803
I finished all of today's deliveries,
so please stop being mad.

78
00:08:54,555 --> 00:08:59,185
What good is delivering
a 70th birthday congratulatory wreath

79
00:08:59,894 --> 00:09:01,270
after the party's over?

80
00:09:02,647 --> 00:09:04,857
Well wishes on their road to their 80th?

81
00:09:06,942 --> 00:09:10,780
I'm holding back because I don't want
to raise Cheong without a father,

82
00:09:10,863 --> 00:09:13,157
but I have limits, too, you know.

83
00:09:14,325 --> 00:09:18,746
Look, I really was planning on
working very hard this morning,

84
00:09:18,829 --> 00:09:21,624
but my friend's father
passed away today, of all days.

85
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:26,462
Everyone knows
that you don't have any friends.

86
00:09:27,588 --> 00:09:30,341
How do the fathers
of all those imaginary friends of yours

87
00:09:30,424 --> 00:09:32,426
manage to keep passing away?

88
00:09:33,844 --> 00:09:38,349
A lot of them are from blended families,
so naturally, they have two fathers.

89
00:09:43,229 --> 00:09:44,063
Aren't you coming?

90
00:09:44,814 --> 00:09:45,856
You go ahead.

91
00:09:46,357 --> 00:09:48,275
I'll head home after wiping this down.

92
00:10:03,457 --> 00:10:04,542
Damn it.

93
00:10:06,127 --> 00:10:07,294
Oh, come on.

94
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:10,756
Goddammit!

95
00:10:11,716 --> 00:10:14,468
Damn it all!

96
00:10:14,552 --> 00:10:16,804
I'm not done wiping.
Did you forget something?

97
00:10:24,437 --> 00:10:26,188
<i>I think a new variant has appeared.</i>

98
00:10:27,356 --> 00:10:29,400
<i>I need to know what's going on.</i>

99
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:30,985
<i>Please contact me.</i>

100
00:10:36,532 --> 00:10:37,366
DELETE

101
00:10:50,504 --> 00:10:51,756
<i>What is it now?</i>

102
00:10:52,339 --> 00:10:54,300
Something's strange with you, isn't it?

103
00:10:56,093 --> 00:10:57,136
What a load of bull.

104
00:10:58,971 --> 00:11:01,515
Did you see the hole
Ro-bin made in the wall with a can?

105
00:11:02,183 --> 00:11:03,851
And I keep vanishing into thin air.

106
00:11:03,934 --> 00:11:07,521
I zoom from place to place
in the blink of an eye.

107
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:10,649
Why are you barging into my shop
and spouting this nonsense?

108
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:13,360
Do I look like I have time to waste
like you two? Leave!

109
00:11:13,861 --> 00:11:15,613
I have to finish wiping this pot.

110
00:11:15,696 --> 00:11:20,117
I swear I almost got shot earlier
in the middle of the ocean.

111
00:11:20,201 --> 00:11:21,619
Look, a bullet hole.

112
00:11:22,745 --> 00:11:25,581
Are you okay? Is there nothing strange
going on with you?

113
00:11:27,291 --> 00:11:30,419
I'm so normal that I couldn't possibly be
more normal than I am now.

114
00:11:30,503 --> 00:11:33,506
So please don't lump me in
with the likes of you.

115
00:11:33,589 --> 00:11:36,425
I'm built differently from you two!

116
00:11:40,095 --> 00:11:41,013
The heck?

117
00:11:42,973 --> 00:11:44,892
What, are you stuck?

118
00:11:48,354 --> 00:11:50,648
You're stuck like glue, aren't you?

119
00:11:50,731 --> 00:11:52,316
Come on!

120
00:11:55,861 --> 00:11:58,113
Mr. Son, did you turn into flypaper?

121
00:11:58,197 --> 00:11:59,323
I told you I'm not--

122
00:12:04,119 --> 00:12:06,497
I think there's something wrong
with all of us.

123
00:12:06,997 --> 00:12:09,416
Maybe someone sprayed pesticide
in our neighborhood.

124
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,669
Or perhaps they put a curse on us?

125
00:12:12,253 --> 00:12:14,046
Others would call these sorts of things

126
00:12:15,005 --> 00:12:16,090
superpowers.

127
00:12:16,173 --> 00:12:17,508
No!

128
00:12:17,591 --> 00:12:19,468
Let's just call it a curse.

129
00:12:20,052 --> 00:12:21,679
Phenol. Yeah, that damn phenol!

130
00:12:22,471 --> 00:12:25,224
We've been cursed
by the 20th-century Industrial Revolution.

131
00:12:25,307 --> 00:12:26,475
These aren't superpowers!

132
00:12:26,559 --> 00:12:29,228
No! They're superpowers.

133
00:12:30,271 --> 00:12:32,106
There's no other explanation.

134
00:12:32,982 --> 00:12:34,233
This is insane!

135
00:12:34,316 --> 00:12:35,568
I knew something was wrong

136
00:12:36,068 --> 00:12:39,822
when I saw that pigeon's eyes
blinking sideways--

137
00:12:40,531 --> 00:12:41,824
Don't do that!

138
00:12:42,575 --> 00:12:45,202
You two. Not a peep about any of this.

139
00:12:45,286 --> 00:12:47,413
Your lips are sealed, no matter the cost.

140
00:12:47,496 --> 00:12:48,330
Why?

141
00:12:48,831 --> 00:12:51,208
Would we be carted away
and experimented on?

142
00:12:51,292 --> 00:12:52,793
Wouldn't that be nice!

143
00:12:53,294 --> 00:12:56,755
People already call me a royal nightmare
for associating with you two.

144
00:12:56,839 --> 00:13:00,801
What would they think of me
if word got out that things stick to me?

145
00:13:01,302 --> 00:13:02,678
My daughter, Cheong…

146
00:13:03,345 --> 00:13:04,847
And my darling Ms. Moon Mi-hui…

147
00:13:05,931 --> 00:13:07,933
I'm still Cheong's dad

148
00:13:08,434 --> 00:13:09,935
and the head of my household!

149
00:13:12,313 --> 00:13:14,732
I'll keep my family safe.

150
00:13:15,232 --> 00:13:16,317
You got that?

151
00:13:19,445 --> 00:13:20,362
Is anyone here

152
00:13:21,196 --> 00:13:23,449
against you keeping your family safe?

153
00:13:23,532 --> 00:13:24,992
That's right, you punks!

154
00:13:25,075 --> 00:13:26,535
I'll keep my family safe,

155
00:13:26,619 --> 00:13:29,413
so you two stay quiet
and keep this a secret, okay?

156
00:13:31,332 --> 00:13:32,625
What exactly did you see?

157
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:34,710
What? What do you mean, what did I see?

158
00:13:34,793 --> 00:13:36,754
You're freaking out right now.

159
00:13:37,755 --> 00:13:40,883
What is it?
What's got you spooked? What did you see?

160
00:13:46,263 --> 00:13:47,473
Tell us!

161
00:13:47,556 --> 00:13:48,599
Hey.

162
00:13:48,682 --> 00:13:50,768
Or we'll just tell the whole neighborhood!

163
00:13:50,851 --> 00:13:53,604
Mr. Son, the Royal Nightmare,
has turned into human flypaper!

164
00:13:53,687 --> 00:13:54,813
Let go, damn it!

165
00:13:55,731 --> 00:13:56,941
You almost died!

166
00:13:58,984 --> 00:14:01,904
Mr. Oddball almost killed you!

167
00:14:10,871 --> 00:14:15,250
Yikes, look at those dark clouds
suddenly rolling in.

168
00:14:17,461 --> 00:14:21,840
In movies, doesn't something terrible
happen at moments like this?

169
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,979
Please grab a ticket and wait--

170
00:14:39,108 --> 00:14:40,734
What brings you here today?

171
00:14:44,029 --> 00:14:45,781
Are you sure you want me to say

172
00:14:46,532 --> 00:14:47,741
what brought me here?

173
00:14:49,034 --> 00:14:49,868
Go ahead.

174
00:14:51,495 --> 00:14:55,082
What you did to me yesterday
in that abandoned greenhouse…

175
00:14:58,585 --> 00:15:02,881
I considered calling the cops,
but I figured I should hear you out first.

176
00:15:05,134 --> 00:15:07,011
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

177
00:15:08,721 --> 00:15:10,889
Then should I make it clearer for you?

178
00:15:10,973 --> 00:15:13,100
That thing you launched at me yesterday.

179
00:15:15,394 --> 00:15:16,395
Su…

180
00:15:18,439 --> 00:15:19,440
per…

181
00:15:20,899 --> 00:15:23,318
I'm sorry.
We can't help you with that here.

182
00:15:26,238 --> 00:15:27,698
Next, please!

183
00:15:30,325 --> 00:15:31,535
Next, please!

184
00:15:59,188 --> 00:16:01,106
Shouldn't we help him?

185
00:16:01,732 --> 00:16:04,234
Lady Trainwreck is too much
for a rookie to handle.

186
00:16:04,318 --> 00:16:05,527
We'll raise him strong.

187
00:16:05,611 --> 00:16:09,031
If Un-jeong overcomes this,
he will become a civil complaints master.

188
00:16:11,283 --> 00:16:12,618
Mr. Yang!

189
00:16:13,118 --> 00:16:14,953
Should I set up the main hall now?

190
00:16:15,037 --> 00:16:16,622
No, we'll do it this afternoon.

191
00:16:16,705 --> 00:16:18,540
What about dog poop pickup at the park?

192
00:16:18,624 --> 00:16:20,959
Mr. Lee and Team A will take care of that.

193
00:16:21,043 --> 00:16:22,961
What about the street clean-up drive?

194
00:16:23,045 --> 00:16:25,798
That's this Friday.
I told you to put a team together first.

195
00:16:25,881 --> 00:16:28,467
The area is too big
for one person to handle alone.

196
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:29,802
Look here!

197
00:16:29,885 --> 00:16:32,930
Are all the Civil Complaints Office staff
away or something?

198
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:38,185
In Haedeul-ri, Mr. Yang!
The complaint about the stench!

199
00:16:38,268 --> 00:16:40,854
It's far, and no vehicles
are available today.

200
00:16:40,938 --> 00:16:42,773
The buses don't run often either.

201
00:16:42,856 --> 00:16:44,525
That's fine. I'll go.

202
00:16:44,608 --> 00:16:46,401
Are you closed or what?

203
00:16:46,485 --> 00:16:48,403
Is this how you treat your visitors?

204
00:16:48,904 --> 00:16:49,822
All right, then.

205
00:16:49,905 --> 00:16:53,200
First thing is to find the source
of the stench, so go. Hurry.

206
00:16:53,283 --> 00:16:55,077
-Go, quickly. Go on!
-Yes, sir.

207
00:16:57,955 --> 00:16:58,789
OUT ON BUSINESS

208
00:17:08,924 --> 00:17:10,342
Chae-ni will be okay, right?

209
00:17:10,926 --> 00:17:13,762
The city hall is packed.
He wouldn't try anything here.

210
00:17:20,227 --> 00:17:22,062
Mr. Son, quick! Start the car!

211
00:17:22,146 --> 00:17:23,397
Hey, what? Wait.

212
00:17:23,897 --> 00:17:25,399
Chae-ni, are you okay?

213
00:17:25,482 --> 00:17:26,817
Did he attack you at all?

214
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:29,194
See if you still have
all your fingers and toes.

215
00:17:29,695 --> 00:17:32,698
If you're so worried,
why'd you let me go in alone?

216
00:17:32,781 --> 00:17:35,159
I tried to stop you.
You chose not to listen.

217
00:17:36,618 --> 00:17:38,078
What did City Hall Guy say?

218
00:17:38,162 --> 00:17:41,331
Why did he shoot that energy blast at you?
Is it really a superpower?

219
00:17:41,415 --> 00:17:42,791
Or is it some kind of disease?

220
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:45,419
Why didn't you ask
whether we're just stuck with it

221
00:17:45,502 --> 00:17:49,339
or if the government has
some kind of plan or compensation?

222
00:17:49,423 --> 00:17:51,633
That's why I need you to tail him,
so I can ask!

223
00:17:51,717 --> 00:17:52,759
Fine.

224
00:17:53,343 --> 00:17:56,054
Go, hurry! That way, hurry!

225
00:17:56,138 --> 00:17:56,972
Step on it!

226
00:18:10,903 --> 00:18:14,364
We contacted you, ma'am,
because his entire family is abroad.

227
00:18:14,865 --> 00:18:16,867
A suicide note was found at the scene.

228
00:18:17,451 --> 00:18:18,869
It was addressed to you.

229
00:18:19,453 --> 00:18:20,412
A suicide note?

230
00:18:22,915 --> 00:18:24,958
You mean that
Director Choi committed suicide?

231
00:18:29,546 --> 00:18:30,672
Why don't you read it?

232
00:18:33,008 --> 00:18:34,885
TO MS. KIM JEON-BOK

233
00:18:40,265 --> 00:18:42,434
<i>Dr. Ha Won-do is innocent.</i>

234
00:18:43,143 --> 00:18:45,229
<i>He was an honorable scholar.</i>

235
00:18:46,063 --> 00:18:48,523
<i>You people are the ones who have sinned.</i>

236
00:18:49,066 --> 00:18:51,360
<i>May you beg Dr. Ha Won-do for forgiveness.</i>

237
00:18:59,201 --> 00:19:00,577
Director Choi.

238
00:19:01,536 --> 00:19:03,330
Let me ask you one last time.

239
00:19:05,207 --> 00:19:07,251
Where is the Child of Eternity?

240
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:16,385
Answer him.

241
00:19:29,648 --> 00:19:31,066
Hearty House…

242
00:19:34,361 --> 00:19:35,445
Madam King.

243
00:20:13,775 --> 00:20:18,238
<i>Early this morning, there was an explosion</i>
<i>at an orphanage in Haeseong.</i>

244
00:20:18,322 --> 00:20:20,949
<i>The fire department</i>
<i>responded immediately to the call,</i>

245
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:24,536
<i>but the flames were difficult</i>
<i>to extinguish.</i>

246
00:20:24,619 --> 00:20:28,623
<i>While searching the charred orphanage,</i>
<i>the fire department and police…</i>

247
00:20:28,707 --> 00:20:32,252
<i>The children discovered in the lab</i>
<i>are currently in treatment</i>

248
00:20:32,336 --> 00:20:34,046
<i>with relevant government support.</i>

249
00:20:34,129 --> 00:20:38,508
<i>The chief of the lab is Dr. Ha Won-do,</i>
<i>a specialist in cell regeneration.</i>

250
00:20:38,592 --> 00:20:41,553
<i>He is suspected</i>
<i>of conducting illegal clinical trials</i>

251
00:20:41,636 --> 00:20:43,305
<i>on the children at the orphanage.</i>

252
00:20:43,388 --> 00:20:45,849
<i>The police stated</i>
<i>they will investigate the researchers</i>

253
00:20:45,932 --> 00:20:48,185
<i>who were involved in the experiments.</i>

254
00:20:48,268 --> 00:20:50,312
Dr. Ha Won-do! Please say a few words!

255
00:20:50,395 --> 00:20:51,730
-Stand back!
-Dr. Ha Won-do!

256
00:20:53,357 --> 00:20:54,232
THE HOLY BIBLE

257
00:21:14,211 --> 00:21:15,253
Hello, ma'am.

258
00:21:15,837 --> 00:21:16,922
Can I help you?

259
00:21:17,005 --> 00:21:18,924
We've received a missing persons report.

260
00:21:28,892 --> 00:21:31,311
Even family members
often struggle to see eye to eye

261
00:21:31,395 --> 00:21:33,647
when they follow different religions.

262
00:21:35,482 --> 00:21:37,818
But to claim that we imprison runaways…

263
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:40,112
That's just ridiculous.

264
00:21:42,447 --> 00:21:46,326
Everyone here has come
of their own free will.

265
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:50,914
We're obligated to check out all reports.
Thank you for understanding.

266
00:21:52,249 --> 00:21:53,375
Please take your time.

267
00:22:01,466 --> 00:22:03,844
This place is huge.

268
00:22:04,803 --> 00:22:08,056
-Anyway, thank you for your cooperation.
-Oh, it's nothing.

269
00:22:10,308 --> 00:22:12,144
Is there a basement here?

270
00:22:17,607 --> 00:22:18,859
Would you like a look?

271
00:22:34,207 --> 00:22:36,042
Just look at you.

272
00:22:36,710 --> 00:22:37,878
Kim Bong-pal.

273
00:22:38,378 --> 00:22:40,714
I never got to pay back your 5,000 won.

274
00:22:45,051 --> 00:22:46,052
It's the police!

275
00:22:46,845 --> 00:22:48,263
Officers!

276
00:22:48,805 --> 00:22:50,182
Mr. Officer!

277
00:22:50,265 --> 00:22:53,477
Here! Please save me!

278
00:22:54,144 --> 00:22:57,814
This is an area we've set up
for our believers to rest.

279
00:23:13,788 --> 00:23:14,831
Wow.

280
00:23:20,504 --> 00:23:23,381
It must have cost a fortune
to set this up.

281
00:23:28,553 --> 00:23:31,181
These tropical fish look expensive too.

282
00:23:32,516 --> 00:23:34,351
I saw them in a picture book as a kid.

283
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:36,394
Sorry?

284
00:23:39,564 --> 00:23:40,982
Right, I see.

285
00:23:49,699 --> 00:23:51,868
Here, I'm in here.

286
00:23:51,952 --> 00:23:54,871
Please get me out of here!

287
00:23:54,955 --> 00:23:56,706
Hey, Mr. Police Officer!

288
00:23:58,083 --> 00:23:59,042
I'm over here!

289
00:23:59,125 --> 00:24:01,336
Hey!

290
00:24:01,419 --> 00:24:04,422
Hey, get me out of here!

291
00:24:04,506 --> 00:24:06,007
That's it. Over here.

292
00:24:07,008 --> 00:24:08,593
Here!

293
00:24:09,094 --> 00:24:10,136
This way!

294
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:12,222
Where are you looking? I said here!

295
00:24:12,305 --> 00:24:14,015
Yes, that's it.

296
00:24:14,641 --> 00:24:15,684
Get me out.

297
00:24:23,984 --> 00:24:24,859
Here!

298
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,112
Get me out. Hey, what…

299
00:24:27,612 --> 00:24:30,365
I said get me out of here! Please!

300
00:24:31,116 --> 00:24:33,535
Would you like to look around some more?

301
00:24:33,618 --> 00:24:34,953
Hello?

302
00:24:35,787 --> 00:24:38,248
No, I think we've seen more than enough.

303
00:24:38,331 --> 00:24:39,416
Let's go.

304
00:24:39,499 --> 00:24:40,542
Yes, sir.

305
00:24:40,625 --> 00:24:41,501
If you say so.

306
00:24:42,711 --> 00:24:45,672
No, don't go!

307
00:24:45,755 --> 00:24:47,549
Please help me!

308
00:24:47,632 --> 00:24:50,135
Hey, you!

309
00:24:51,136 --> 00:24:53,263
Help me!

310
00:24:59,311 --> 00:25:02,397
Doesn't the next bus to Haedeul-ri
come in two hours?

311
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:04,733
Yeah, and the forecast said
it'll rain today.

312
00:25:04,816 --> 00:25:06,651
Oh dear, looks like it's going to pour.

313
00:25:06,735 --> 00:25:09,070
My questions are about to pour out too.

314
00:25:09,613 --> 00:25:11,031
About the phenol poisoning

315
00:25:11,114 --> 00:25:12,991
and whether we're just stuck with it,

316
00:25:13,074 --> 00:25:16,244
or if there's some kind of plan
or compensation from the government.

317
00:25:18,163 --> 00:25:21,333
We have all the time in the world.
How about a game of acrostics?

318
00:25:21,416 --> 00:25:22,375
-Sure.
-I'm in.

319
00:25:22,459 --> 00:25:23,543
Start me off.

320
00:25:23,627 --> 00:25:25,378
How about… Su!

321
00:25:25,962 --> 00:25:27,088
Super spooked.

322
00:25:27,172 --> 00:25:28,006
Per…

323
00:25:28,089 --> 00:25:29,215
Perplexing powers.

324
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:31,051
Power!

325
00:25:34,679 --> 00:25:36,723
Powerful predicament, eh?

326
00:25:39,184 --> 00:25:41,061
Not bad. Hey, careful with that knife.

327
00:25:41,144 --> 00:25:43,229
I have one too. Kang Ro-bin, hit me.

328
00:25:43,313 --> 00:25:44,147
Su!

329
00:25:44,230 --> 00:25:45,565
Super anxious, aren't you?

330
00:25:46,149 --> 00:25:46,983
Per!

331
00:25:47,067 --> 00:25:49,319
Perhaps because we found out
you have superpowers.

332
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:50,904
Power!

333
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:53,782
Powerful predicament, eh?

334
00:25:55,116 --> 00:25:56,910
Hey, don't wave that knife around.

335
00:25:58,703 --> 00:26:00,664
I said be careful. You'll hurt someone.

336
00:26:00,747 --> 00:26:01,790
High-five!

337
00:26:03,917 --> 00:26:07,045
What? Thinking of shooting
another energy blast at me?

338
00:26:07,629 --> 00:26:10,173
Don't provoke him.
He might blast you to smithereens.

339
00:26:11,758 --> 00:26:15,261
Let's see you try, then.
We won't back down that easily.

340
00:26:15,345 --> 00:26:16,179
Sure.

341
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:17,764
I'll back down, then.

342
00:26:20,725 --> 00:26:22,477
Ms. Eun Chae-ni. Excuse me!

343
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:24,521
My bag! Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

344
00:26:27,190 --> 00:26:28,942
Ms. Eun Chae-ni. Give me--

345
00:26:29,442 --> 00:26:31,194
What the… Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

346
00:26:31,695 --> 00:26:33,029
What do you think you're--

347
00:26:34,823 --> 00:26:39,452
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

348
00:26:53,425 --> 00:26:54,968
I'm glad that ended well.

349
00:26:55,844 --> 00:26:59,097
Getting mixed up with religious groups
is always a headache.

350
00:27:01,015 --> 00:27:03,727
What's this stuff you've had on
since yesterday?

351
00:27:03,810 --> 00:27:06,980
I didn't put anything on.
I've just been sweating the past few days.

352
00:27:11,484 --> 00:27:14,612
Hey, this isn't sweat!
You've covered yourself in something!

353
00:27:14,696 --> 00:27:16,364
I'm telling you, it's sweat.

354
00:27:18,533 --> 00:27:21,411
-Maybe I ate something odd.
-Let's get going.

355
00:27:35,967 --> 00:27:38,928
-My heart's healthier.
-Can someone like me gain superpowers too?

356
00:27:39,012 --> 00:27:41,389
-Will I stay healthy?
-Uri Geller, the magic guy…

357
00:27:41,473 --> 00:27:43,433
-Will we be vivisected?
-Or lose our powers?

358
00:27:43,516 --> 00:27:45,560
-He earned a fortune.
-How come I'm healthier?

359
00:27:45,643 --> 00:27:46,978
In this economy, you need to…

360
00:27:47,061 --> 00:27:48,813
-I just don't get why--
-Excuse me.

361
00:27:50,607 --> 00:27:52,525
I can't hear a word you're saying.

362
00:27:53,026 --> 00:27:55,445
If you all talk at once,
how can I understand--

363
00:27:55,528 --> 00:27:59,157
We've told you earlier
that all three of us now have superpowers.

364
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:01,701
Mr. Son sticks to things.
He busts holes in walls.

365
00:28:01,785 --> 00:28:03,453
And I teleport in a flash.

366
00:28:04,746 --> 00:28:06,498
I still can't understand you.

367
00:28:06,581 --> 00:28:10,043
Look here. Do you really think
I didn't see anything?

368
00:28:10,752 --> 00:28:12,212
That thing you did…

369
00:28:12,295 --> 00:28:14,380
You're not Mr. Oddball
but Mr. Energy Blast.

370
00:28:14,464 --> 00:28:17,342
You seemed to control your power at will.

371
00:28:17,425 --> 00:28:21,763
The least you can do is tell us
how to control ours too.

372
00:28:21,846 --> 00:28:25,642
Yes, sir, please tell us.
We're all going to be okay, right?

373
00:28:26,643 --> 00:28:28,102
I'm terrified.

374
00:28:31,356 --> 00:28:32,482
Look.

375
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:39,030
I thought you'd use your powers
in a pinch. Guess not.

376
00:28:39,113 --> 00:28:41,616
You're slower than you look.

377
00:28:41,699 --> 00:28:43,701
You just wanted to throw that at me.

378
00:28:43,785 --> 00:28:44,786
Okay, fine.

379
00:28:45,286 --> 00:28:47,622
I won't ask you to demonstrate.

380
00:28:47,705 --> 00:28:50,166
Just tell me what's going on here.

381
00:28:51,042 --> 00:28:54,379
Then I'll forget about you blasting me
with your energy.

382
00:28:54,879 --> 00:28:58,091
If you tell me everything,
I'll even call you Master.

383
00:29:01,594 --> 00:29:04,514
I don't know what you saw
and what misconception you have,

384
00:29:05,014 --> 00:29:08,518
but I don't think I can help you
with this complaint. I'm sorry.

385
00:29:11,312 --> 00:29:14,941
So, you're telling us
to figure this out by ourselves.

386
00:29:19,195 --> 00:29:20,113
Yes.

387
00:29:22,907 --> 00:29:23,908
-That's it.
-Get out.

388
00:29:23,992 --> 00:29:26,703
<i>You </i>kidnapped <i>me</i>.
You can't just ditch me like--

389
00:29:26,786 --> 00:29:28,079
Where are we, anyway?

390
00:29:29,247 --> 00:29:30,874
At least tell me where we are!

391
00:29:30,957 --> 00:29:32,125
Deary me, what a shame.

392
00:29:32,208 --> 00:29:34,919
I don't think
I can help you with that question.

393
00:29:35,003 --> 00:29:38,006
Kang Ro-bin, what are you doing?
Man, this guy won't give up!

394
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,592
Man, he's strong.

395
00:29:43,678 --> 00:29:44,929
What the…

396
00:29:45,013 --> 00:29:47,807
Hey, Gyeong-hwan!

397
00:29:47,891 --> 00:29:48,725
Gyeong-hwan!

398
00:29:48,808 --> 00:29:50,268
What's wrong with you, man?

399
00:29:50,351 --> 00:29:51,644
Snap out of it!

400
00:29:51,728 --> 00:29:53,730
Hey, Gyeong-hwan!

401
00:30:02,322 --> 00:30:06,492
-It's smoking. Watch out for the glass!
-What if it explodes soon?

402
00:30:06,576 --> 00:30:10,330
-Okay, three, two, one!
-Quick, hurry!

403
00:30:10,830 --> 00:30:12,373
Let's help him up first.

404
00:30:12,457 --> 00:30:14,083
-Hurry!
-That's it!

405
00:30:14,167 --> 00:30:15,877
Is he conscious or what?

406
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,670
I guess not. Hurry!

407
00:30:17,754 --> 00:30:18,588
Go, yeah.

408
00:30:19,881 --> 00:30:20,882
He weighs a ton.

409
00:30:23,259 --> 00:30:26,304
Mister, your hand! Darn, I can't reach.

410
00:30:27,597 --> 00:30:29,557
Ro-bin! Kang Ro-bin, get over here!

411
00:30:32,685 --> 00:30:34,562
Man, this is scary. Really scary.

412
00:30:34,646 --> 00:30:35,730
Hey, mister.

413
00:30:35,813 --> 00:30:37,315
Wake up, will you?

414
00:30:37,398 --> 00:30:39,359
Are you dead? That's not good.

415
00:30:42,946 --> 00:30:44,614
Why's his arm like this?

416
00:30:45,448 --> 00:30:46,324
Is it broken?

417
00:30:46,407 --> 00:30:48,034
-This is…
-He's so sweaty.

418
00:30:48,117 --> 00:30:49,702
What is this?

419
00:30:49,786 --> 00:30:52,372
-Hey, mister! Be careful.
-We need to save him!

420
00:30:52,872 --> 00:30:54,540
Quick.

421
00:31:02,632 --> 00:31:04,175
We'll get him from below.

422
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:06,719
-Fire!
-There's a fire!

423
00:31:06,803 --> 00:31:08,471
Step back. It's dangerous!

424
00:31:09,180 --> 00:31:10,014
What do we do?

425
00:31:11,516 --> 00:31:13,226
Those two never goddamn listen!

426
00:31:14,185 --> 00:31:15,019
Push.

427
00:31:16,229 --> 00:31:17,480
What are you doing?

428
00:31:17,563 --> 00:31:19,482
Are you gonna just stand there and watch?

429
00:31:26,239 --> 00:31:28,408
Are you really not going to help us?

430
00:31:28,491 --> 00:31:32,245
Why be stingy with your powers?
Gonna buy a house with them or something?

431
00:31:32,328 --> 00:31:34,914
Are you sure you even have a superpower?

432
00:31:34,998 --> 00:31:38,251
Hey, stop that and get over here!
It's going to blow!

433
00:31:38,334 --> 00:31:41,045
First responders will be here soon.
Why are you doing that?

434
00:31:41,129 --> 00:31:44,465
It's always the reckless ones
who have to make everything a production.

435
00:31:44,549 --> 00:31:48,344
Do you always have to be so insufferable?

436
00:31:49,679 --> 00:31:52,473
At least go get some water
to put out the fire!

437
00:31:55,018 --> 00:31:56,686
Where am I supposed to get water?

438
00:31:56,769 --> 00:32:00,732
I'm not doing this because you told me to.
It's for the public good, okay?

439
00:32:02,275 --> 00:32:04,861
I guess I'll have to walk around.

440
00:32:07,947 --> 00:32:09,615
It won't budge.

441
00:32:30,928 --> 00:32:32,847
Hey, Chae-ni, I got my strength back!

442
00:32:35,850 --> 00:32:37,727
I… I'm…

443
00:32:39,771 --> 00:32:40,897
I'm…

444
00:32:41,481 --> 00:32:42,982
I'm useful now!

445
00:32:43,566 --> 00:32:45,276
Now that I have this power,

446
00:32:46,027 --> 00:32:47,945
I'm useful, Chae-ni!

447
00:32:48,029 --> 00:32:49,864
Wow, yeah.

448
00:32:49,947 --> 00:32:52,116
You're amazing, Kang Ro-bin!

449
00:32:54,285 --> 00:32:56,579
Keep using your powers,
the amazing Kang Ro-bin.

450
00:32:57,413 --> 00:32:58,331
Okay.

451
00:33:01,042 --> 00:33:04,128
Who taught her
to speak so disrespectfully?

452
00:33:10,510 --> 00:33:11,803
You bastard!

453
00:33:43,793 --> 00:33:45,128
I'll save you, mister.

454
00:33:45,211 --> 00:33:47,630
But what is this? Why is he so slippery?

455
00:33:47,713 --> 00:33:49,632
Mister, you're still alive, right?

456
00:33:49,715 --> 00:33:50,883
You'd better be.

457
00:33:50,967 --> 00:33:52,343
You can't die, mister.

458
00:33:52,426 --> 00:33:54,512
Even if you can't come to your senses…

459
00:33:54,595 --> 00:33:56,597
You're badly hurt. Oh no, what do we do?

460
00:34:11,362 --> 00:34:12,738
Great job, Kang Ro-bin.

461
00:34:13,990 --> 00:34:15,700
You were pretty darn cool.

462
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,079
A carp!

463
00:34:20,580 --> 00:34:21,414
Guys!

464
00:34:21,497 --> 00:34:23,875
I saw a carp…
Why are his arms so freaking long?

465
00:34:23,958 --> 00:34:26,169
Just put out the fire already!

466
00:34:33,467 --> 00:34:34,719
Hey, a carp…

467
00:34:35,219 --> 00:34:36,929
A carp as big as me

468
00:34:37,013 --> 00:34:39,682
looked my way, then flashed me a wink.

469
00:34:39,765 --> 00:34:43,144
Mr. Son, I just lifted this car.

470
00:34:43,227 --> 00:34:46,314
I'm dead serious!
I really saw a carp as big as me.

471
00:34:46,397 --> 00:34:49,192
It even had lashes on its eyelids!

472
00:34:49,275 --> 00:34:51,694
Funny how you're the only one
who sees these things.

473
00:34:51,777 --> 00:34:53,154
What are the odds?

474
00:34:54,488 --> 00:34:56,616
Are you calling me a liar right now?

475
00:34:57,283 --> 00:34:59,827
I've never lied in my entire life.
How dare you…

476
00:35:02,163 --> 00:35:03,414
What's going on here?

477
00:35:07,668 --> 00:35:08,544
Now?

478
00:35:13,799 --> 00:35:14,759
Of all times…

479
00:35:17,178 --> 00:35:19,847
Mr. Son, what are you doing? Let go of me!

480
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:22,141
Hey, I really want to let go too.

481
00:35:23,267 --> 00:35:24,852
What? Are they stuck?

482
00:35:25,519 --> 00:35:26,395
No way.

483
00:35:26,896 --> 00:35:27,730
For real?

484
00:35:31,442 --> 00:35:32,276
Damn it!

485
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:35,154
Get it off. Hurry! Pull it off!

486
00:35:35,238 --> 00:35:37,406
How are you meant to get it off?

487
00:35:37,490 --> 00:35:40,034
No, get off!

488
00:35:40,117 --> 00:35:41,035
This can't be.

489
00:35:41,702 --> 00:35:42,578
Get off!

490
00:35:43,079 --> 00:35:43,996
Get off!

491
00:35:45,248 --> 00:35:46,832
Aren't you gonna do something?

492
00:35:46,916 --> 00:35:48,960
At this rate, they'll be roasted whole!

493
00:35:53,798 --> 00:35:56,550
Seriously, do something, Mr. Son!

494
00:35:57,677 --> 00:35:59,679
What the…
Mr. Oddball, what did you just do?

495
00:35:59,762 --> 00:36:01,430
If you're doing it, do it right!

496
00:36:01,514 --> 00:36:04,058
Do you really even have a superpower?

497
00:36:05,434 --> 00:36:08,104
Come on, what are you doing?
The fire's spreading!

498
00:36:08,187 --> 00:36:10,231
Get Mr. Son off of there already!

499
00:36:29,166 --> 00:36:31,294
What about me?

500
00:36:32,461 --> 00:36:33,504
Mr. Son!

501
00:36:34,088 --> 00:36:36,424
-Get to safety now!
-What about you, Mr. Son?

502
00:36:36,507 --> 00:36:40,052
There's no way I'm dying here.
No way in hell!

503
00:36:40,594 --> 00:36:43,597
So get to safety now, you little shit!

504
00:36:43,681 --> 00:36:45,433
You never goddamn listen!

505
00:36:46,517 --> 00:36:47,351
Mr. Son.

506
00:36:49,937 --> 00:36:51,063
No way.

507
00:36:51,564 --> 00:36:53,190
Is Mr. Son really going to die?

508
00:36:56,610 --> 00:37:00,114
That's not right!
After all the miserable things he's done?

509
00:37:02,033 --> 00:37:03,242
I won't let that happen.

510
00:37:03,993 --> 00:37:06,120
If you die, it'll be by my hands--

511
00:37:09,832 --> 00:37:11,584
Mr. Son!

512
00:37:11,667 --> 00:37:13,044
Get away!

513
00:37:19,383 --> 00:37:20,301
I said go!

514
00:37:20,885 --> 00:37:23,846
Go get someone else. Anyone but you.

515
00:37:24,430 --> 00:37:28,017
What are you… Just hurry up and go.

516
00:37:28,100 --> 00:37:30,269
I could do it just moments ago.

517
00:37:30,353 --> 00:37:33,314
I had a superpower too!

518
00:37:34,774 --> 00:37:38,986
At this rate, we'll both die!

519
00:37:39,904 --> 00:37:41,697
Why does it have to be you?

520
00:37:42,448 --> 00:37:45,159
Why are you the one here with me
at a moment like this?

521
00:37:45,242 --> 00:37:49,997
Why you, the most useless person
in the entire world?

522
00:37:50,081 --> 00:37:52,666
I told you to stop being so mean!

523
00:38:00,383 --> 00:38:01,342
Try that again?

524
00:38:09,683 --> 00:38:10,684
Fire!

525
00:38:31,664 --> 00:38:33,332
Let's cut his arm off with this!

526
00:38:37,420 --> 00:38:38,546
You're alive?

527
00:38:41,465 --> 00:38:42,550
Hey!

528
00:38:43,050 --> 00:38:44,176
You're alive!

529
00:38:45,136 --> 00:38:46,804
Kang Ro-bin, you…

530
00:38:48,013 --> 00:38:48,848
You…

531
00:38:51,892 --> 00:38:53,394
That's right, Mr. Son.

532
00:38:54,019 --> 00:38:56,063
I saved your life.

533
00:38:57,523 --> 00:38:59,233
You have phenol poisoning too.

534
00:39:00,359 --> 00:39:02,027
Phenol, for sure…

535
00:39:09,910 --> 00:39:12,621
So we saved them?

536
00:39:15,916 --> 00:39:17,084
Wow.

537
00:39:17,168 --> 00:39:18,878
We're

538
00:39:19,378 --> 00:39:21,839
pretty awesome, aren't we?

539
00:39:40,149 --> 00:39:41,525
Just look at those flames.

540
00:39:44,528 --> 00:39:45,613
Here's your water.

541
00:39:49,867 --> 00:39:51,660
Any news on what I asked you to check?

542
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:55,623
Director Choi's vacation home
had security cameras,

543
00:39:56,123 --> 00:39:58,042
but all the footage was erased.

544
00:39:58,751 --> 00:40:00,169
They think someone took it.

545
00:40:00,252 --> 00:40:02,379
And they have no idea
who it might've been?

546
00:40:03,714 --> 00:40:07,927
There were no fingerprints or traces.
Even the police are baffled.

547
00:40:08,969 --> 00:40:12,097
Shouldn't you close the restaurant
for a while and go into hiding?

548
00:40:13,349 --> 00:40:16,060
Four people involved in this
are already dead.

549
00:40:16,644 --> 00:40:17,728
Check, please.

550
00:40:18,229 --> 00:40:19,063
Of course.

551
00:40:23,567 --> 00:40:24,568
FLOWERS

552
00:40:31,367 --> 00:40:34,411
But what was up with that cop earlier?

553
00:40:35,037 --> 00:40:38,582
Do you think turning into a floppy monster
is also a superpower?

554
00:40:38,666 --> 00:40:41,168
It means we're not the only ones
who are messed up.

555
00:40:41,252 --> 00:40:43,254
Pigeons, carp,

556
00:40:43,754 --> 00:40:45,464
and now even those cops.

557
00:40:45,548 --> 00:40:48,342
It's proof that our entire town
is getting sick.

558
00:40:51,595 --> 00:40:52,805
So what should we do now?

559
00:40:54,181 --> 00:40:55,516
Why are you asking me?

560
00:40:56,475 --> 00:40:58,894
We've all seen each other's superpowers.

561
00:40:58,978 --> 00:41:00,354
Doesn't that make us a team?

562
00:41:00,437 --> 00:41:02,064
-A team?
-A team?

563
00:41:02,147 --> 00:41:05,818
We saved those two cops, didn't we?
By working together as a team.

564
00:41:05,901 --> 00:41:08,320
We did risk our lives
for zero financial gain.

565
00:41:09,071 --> 00:41:10,239
Wait a minute.

566
00:41:11,824 --> 00:41:14,702
Do you think we could get
some reward money for that?

567
00:41:15,661 --> 00:41:17,913
Whoa, reward money!

568
00:41:17,997 --> 00:41:19,290
Hey, that hurts.

569
00:41:19,373 --> 00:41:23,210
First thing we can do is split that money
four ways. What do you say, City Hall Guy?

570
00:41:23,294 --> 00:41:25,713
No, I'm done here.

571
00:41:32,595 --> 00:41:35,347
You three can deal with
what happened to you on your own.

572
00:41:35,431 --> 00:41:37,391
I don't know what you want from me,

573
00:41:37,474 --> 00:41:39,518
but even if I did, I couldn't help you.

574
00:41:40,394 --> 00:41:41,854
Nor do I care to.

575
00:41:53,949 --> 00:41:57,328
What's he giving us the cold shoulder for?

576
00:41:57,411 --> 00:41:58,412
How heartless.

577
00:41:58,996 --> 00:42:00,789
I guess he really doesn't like us.

578
00:42:00,873 --> 00:42:02,333
Who would?

579
00:42:06,295 --> 00:42:08,297
That's one less mouth to feed though.

580
00:42:08,797 --> 00:42:10,758
About the reward money.

581
00:42:11,634 --> 00:42:13,344
I guess we'll split it three ways?

582
00:42:18,265 --> 00:42:19,099
Shall we?

583
00:42:58,597 --> 00:43:00,265
HAESEONG DRAINAGE PLANS

584
00:43:08,065 --> 00:43:09,441
GYEGO-1-DONG DRAINAGE PLAN

585
00:43:12,069 --> 00:43:12,903
GYEGO-2-DONG

586
00:43:12,986 --> 00:43:14,196
HAEDEUL-RI DRAINAGE PLAN

587
00:43:25,416 --> 00:43:27,126
STORMWATER SEWER WINGWALL

588
00:43:48,856 --> 00:43:49,982
"13 Haedeul-ri."

589
00:43:50,941 --> 00:43:52,276
13 Haedeul-ri…

590
00:44:01,368 --> 00:44:02,828
13 Haejeon-eup.

591
00:44:04,621 --> 00:44:07,875
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION
PRAYER HOUSE

592
00:44:20,429 --> 00:44:22,473
-They're not here?
-How could that be?

593
00:44:23,390 --> 00:44:24,933
They were never even admitted.

594
00:44:25,017 --> 00:44:27,853
No police officers
were brought here today.

595
00:44:27,936 --> 00:44:29,229
Nurse Eom?

596
00:44:29,313 --> 00:44:31,148
Yes, I'm coming!

597
00:44:35,611 --> 00:44:38,113
Didn't they clearly say Haeseong Hospital?

598
00:44:38,197 --> 00:44:40,157
But she said they never came here.

599
00:45:00,844 --> 00:45:03,096
What do you mean you never got the report?

600
00:45:03,597 --> 00:45:05,766
We definitely reported it.

601
00:45:06,266 --> 00:45:08,644
There was a car accident,
then an ambulance came

602
00:45:08,727 --> 00:45:12,022
and took the two injured cops
to Haeseong Hospital.

603
00:45:12,105 --> 00:45:13,524
<i>Maybe you were mistaken.</i>

604
00:45:13,607 --> 00:45:17,152
<i>We have no record of a report from</i>
<i>or dispatch to Haedeul-ri.</i>

605
00:45:17,694 --> 00:45:20,113
<i>And no car accidents</i>
<i>involving police officers.</i>

606
00:45:22,908 --> 00:45:24,117
What is going on?

607
00:45:24,785 --> 00:45:26,453
If there's no record of a report,

608
00:45:26,537 --> 00:45:29,873
who were those paramedics
who took the cops?

609
00:45:30,791 --> 00:45:32,376
Then the cops who were injured,

610
00:45:32,876 --> 00:45:34,586
where did they disappear to?

611
00:45:34,670 --> 00:45:35,754
They must have

612
00:45:36,547 --> 00:45:41,176
been taken by people
who don't want this to get out.

613
00:45:41,927 --> 00:45:45,722
Does that mean if they find out about us,
they'll come and take us too?

614
00:45:45,806 --> 00:45:46,765
Where to?

615
00:45:47,641 --> 00:45:48,517
What if

616
00:45:49,017 --> 00:45:50,894
we get taken somewhere, too,

617
00:45:50,978 --> 00:45:52,855
to get vivisected or something?

618
00:45:52,938 --> 00:45:56,191
Damn. They should at least
put us under first.

619
00:45:56,692 --> 00:45:58,944
I'm scared. Chae-ni, I'm freaking out.

620
00:46:06,493 --> 00:46:07,578
RELIGIOUS FACILITIES

621
00:46:09,162 --> 00:46:12,082
This has nothing to do with me.
Nothing at all.

622
00:47:03,467 --> 00:47:05,344
This area's restricted to staff only.

623
00:47:05,427 --> 00:47:06,720
In life,

624
00:47:07,679 --> 00:47:11,058
people can sometimes lose their way.

625
00:47:12,476 --> 00:47:14,269
They go to places they shouldn't

626
00:47:15,103 --> 00:47:17,147
and look for things they shouldn't.

627
00:47:17,731 --> 00:47:19,691
Unaware that it'll cost them their lives.

628
00:47:21,526 --> 00:47:23,445
Isn't that right, 3972?

629
00:47:30,327 --> 00:47:31,161
Here?

630
00:47:32,371 --> 00:47:34,581
There'd be a lot of casualties.

631
00:47:35,499 --> 00:47:36,458
You okay with that?

632
00:47:42,339 --> 00:47:44,049
Hey, Mr. Lee Un-jeong.

633
00:47:44,132 --> 00:47:47,302
There you are. Talk about great timing.

634
00:47:47,386 --> 00:47:50,097
Can you hurry and set up the partitions
in the main hall?

635
00:47:50,180 --> 00:47:52,933
I have to prep for tomorrow's meeting,
so I don't have time.

636
00:47:54,309 --> 00:47:55,143
Okay, sir.

637
00:47:55,727 --> 00:47:57,479
Great, well…

638
00:47:58,480 --> 00:48:00,816
Where has Mr. Lee Sang-min gone now?

639
00:48:05,070 --> 00:48:06,488
Mr. Lee Un-jeong?

640
00:48:08,115 --> 00:48:10,534
You seem busy, so I'll get to the point.

641
00:48:14,913 --> 00:48:16,832
Why are you back in Haeseong?

642
00:48:16,915 --> 00:48:18,959
Why would a civil servant need a reason?

643
00:48:19,626 --> 00:48:21,378
You go wherever you're assigned.

644
00:48:21,461 --> 00:48:23,338
Did Father…

645
00:48:26,466 --> 00:48:27,592
call you here?

646
00:48:27,676 --> 00:48:28,844
Father?

647
00:48:32,222 --> 00:48:34,933
You still call the man
who made you this way "Father"?

648
00:48:35,017 --> 00:48:37,519
Of course, <i>because </i>he made me this way.

649
00:48:38,603 --> 00:48:39,563
From the weak,

650
00:48:40,063 --> 00:48:41,314
useless,

651
00:48:41,815 --> 00:48:44,359
unwanted Number 4885,

652
00:48:45,444 --> 00:48:47,487
he made me into the Kim Pal-ho I am today.

653
00:48:49,489 --> 00:48:51,575
Father made me feel needed.

654
00:48:52,576 --> 00:48:53,702
He made me strong.

655
00:48:53,785 --> 00:48:56,705
He made you into a monster and used you.

656
00:48:57,289 --> 00:48:58,331
Back then

657
00:48:58,915 --> 00:48:59,750
and now.

658
00:49:01,918 --> 00:49:06,214
I won't bother asking what you
and Dr. Ha Won-do are up to in Haedeul-ri.

659
00:49:06,298 --> 00:49:09,968
I'm not particularly interested,
and I'd rather not get involved.

660
00:49:12,137 --> 00:49:13,305
But don't you think

661
00:49:13,388 --> 00:49:15,474
continuing to create more variants

662
00:49:16,058 --> 00:49:17,392
would be a problem?

663
00:49:19,770 --> 00:49:21,104
Don't you worry.

664
00:49:22,230 --> 00:49:25,025
We're already quietly collecting
the defective ones.

665
00:49:26,526 --> 00:49:27,360
Collecting?

666
00:49:27,444 --> 00:49:29,988
To cleanse the world
and make it beautiful.

667
00:49:33,158 --> 00:49:34,201
Don't you know

668
00:49:34,701 --> 00:49:36,912
that you and I are just like them?

669
00:49:38,038 --> 00:49:38,872
Defects.

670
00:49:40,540 --> 00:49:41,666
No!

671
00:49:42,626 --> 00:49:44,211
We're not.

672
00:49:44,753 --> 00:49:47,380
Why do you think
he called us Wunderkinder?

673
00:49:47,464 --> 00:49:49,716
Because we're miracles, not failures!

674
00:49:49,800 --> 00:49:51,885
We're miracle children!

675
00:50:10,070 --> 00:50:11,363
Go back.

676
00:50:12,864 --> 00:50:14,699
And don't let me ever see you again.

677
00:50:16,034 --> 00:50:17,536
I just want to live a quiet life.

678
00:50:29,089 --> 00:50:30,966
1999 HAESEONG
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATIONS

679
00:50:39,057 --> 00:50:40,642
Forget it. Stop thinking about it.

680
00:50:41,184 --> 00:50:42,978
It's got nothing to do with me.

681
00:50:43,854 --> 00:50:45,981
It's got nothing to do with me.

682
00:50:58,869 --> 00:51:01,163
I just came from Haeseong Hospital.

683
00:51:01,246 --> 00:51:04,040
Those cops have disappeared.

684
00:51:05,208 --> 00:51:08,211
We went through all that trouble
to save them, but they're gone.

685
00:51:08,712 --> 00:51:10,547
No record, and no one remembers them.

686
00:51:11,548 --> 00:51:12,591
What is this?

687
00:51:13,091 --> 00:51:15,719
You know what's going on, don't you?

688
00:51:16,303 --> 00:51:18,763
You're disrupting my work.
Could you please leave?

689
00:51:18,847 --> 00:51:20,223
Will that happen to us too?

690
00:51:22,142 --> 00:51:24,144
Could we disappear without a trace,

691
00:51:24,728 --> 00:51:26,479
just like those officers?

692
00:51:28,773 --> 00:51:29,941
Where would they take us?

693
00:51:31,151 --> 00:51:33,820
Would it be a government agency
like Mr. Nightmare said?

694
00:51:33,904 --> 00:51:37,240
What, are we going to be tortured
or actually vivisected?

695
00:51:38,200 --> 00:51:41,578
That's why you should stay quiet
and lie low, so you can't be found.

696
00:51:42,621 --> 00:51:44,539
Stop congregating and making it obvious.

697
00:51:55,425 --> 00:51:57,135
Let me ask you one thing.

698
00:51:58,345 --> 00:51:59,346
Does this power

699
00:52:00,513 --> 00:52:01,723
have an expiration date?

700
00:52:02,891 --> 00:52:07,896
I may not have died, but I did
come back from the brink of death.

701
00:52:07,979 --> 00:52:11,149
Ever since then,
my body's been strangely healthy.

702
00:52:13,276 --> 00:52:16,446
I don't run out of breath,
I don't bruise, and I don't get sick.

703
00:52:16,529 --> 00:52:18,531
Great, congratulations. Have a nice day.

704
00:52:21,785 --> 00:52:23,703
So I want to know what this power is.

705
00:52:23,787 --> 00:52:26,081
Exactly how I ended up with it

706
00:52:26,164 --> 00:52:27,457
and how to use it.

707
00:52:27,540 --> 00:52:31,586
It's not like I can go out and ask people.
They'd think I'd completely lost it.

708
00:52:32,754 --> 00:52:34,673
If I lose my powers,

709
00:52:36,091 --> 00:52:37,509
will I die again?

710
00:52:46,476 --> 00:52:47,978
You don't know Wunderkinder?

711
00:52:48,061 --> 00:52:50,605
Why do you keep bringing up
that Boon the King Duck?

712
00:52:52,565 --> 00:52:56,319
What is it? Is it a duck
whose genetics were successfully modified?

713
00:52:57,779 --> 00:52:59,239
I was so happy to be alive.

714
00:53:01,533 --> 00:53:02,617
Have I become a duck?

715
00:53:03,201 --> 00:53:04,703
No, it wasn't a success.

716
00:53:05,453 --> 00:53:06,454
It was a failure.

717
00:53:08,999 --> 00:53:09,916
An adverse effect.

718
00:53:11,334 --> 00:53:12,919
Mr. Lee Un-jeong.

719
00:53:18,174 --> 00:53:20,552
It's Kim Na-yeong
from the Welfare Department.

720
00:53:21,511 --> 00:53:22,971
Where are you?

721
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:24,556
You should go.

722
00:53:24,639 --> 00:53:27,684
Not yet. What is
this "Boon the King Duck" thing?

723
00:53:27,767 --> 00:53:29,227
Am I a duck now or not?

724
00:53:29,311 --> 00:53:30,520
You're not, okay?

725
00:53:31,313 --> 00:53:34,065
I have nothing more to say,
so go ask someone else.

726
00:53:37,444 --> 00:53:40,363
Then should I go ask her instead?
What "Boon the King Duck" is?

727
00:53:41,364 --> 00:53:45,035
Should I ask her if she knows anything
since superpower guy here is clueless?

728
00:53:45,118 --> 00:53:47,871
-Un-jeong?
-What, you think I won't?

729
00:53:49,581 --> 00:53:50,415
This guy with su--

730
00:53:58,048 --> 00:54:00,216
You know I wouldn't be
the only one in trouble.

731
00:54:00,884 --> 00:54:01,885
Are you actually dumb?

732
00:54:02,469 --> 00:54:03,303
Dumb?

733
00:54:07,265 --> 00:54:09,309
-Let go of me.
-Quiet.

734
00:54:16,524 --> 00:54:17,901
Mr. Lee Un-jeong?

735
00:54:32,290 --> 00:54:34,167
Oh, there you are.

736
00:54:34,793 --> 00:54:38,671
It's just,
Mr. Yang asked me to help you out.

737
00:54:39,881 --> 00:54:42,133
I'm almost done, so I don't need any help.

738
00:54:45,762 --> 00:54:48,098
What happened to your face? How did that…

739
00:54:49,808 --> 00:54:50,642
I blush easily.

740
00:54:51,559 --> 00:54:53,269
Oh, you blush easily.

741
00:54:54,854 --> 00:54:57,482
The truth is, I came here
because I wanted to help you.

742
00:54:59,067 --> 00:55:03,071
You never come to any
of the staff dinners or get-togethers,

743
00:55:03,571 --> 00:55:06,533
and I've never had the chance
to talk to you alone.

744
00:55:06,616 --> 00:55:09,035
I was hoping you'd show up
to last week's dinner.

745
00:55:12,372 --> 00:55:15,417
Do we just need to line them up properly?

746
00:55:15,500 --> 00:55:16,584
Yes.

747
00:55:20,964 --> 00:55:22,090
That reminds me.

748
00:55:22,173 --> 00:55:24,843
You'll be at the street clean-up drive
this Friday, right?

749
00:55:24,926 --> 00:55:27,470
Have you put a team together yet?
If not, I could…

750
00:55:33,810 --> 00:55:37,313
I'll finish up here. I'll look forward to
seeing you at the street clean-up.

751
00:55:37,397 --> 00:55:38,648
Look forward to?

752
00:55:41,276 --> 00:55:44,112
Will you be joining the team dinner
after the clean-up?

753
00:55:44,195 --> 00:55:45,447
Of course. I'll be there.

754
00:55:46,406 --> 00:55:48,199
All right. See you then.

755
00:56:14,350 --> 00:56:17,437
Could you help me get down?

756
00:56:52,680 --> 00:56:55,350
Why would you hide something like this?

757
00:56:56,100 --> 00:56:56,935
Master!

758
00:57:09,822 --> 00:57:11,699
There's no expiration date.

759
00:57:13,451 --> 00:57:15,495
I almost died the first time too.

760
00:57:19,249 --> 00:57:20,166
Then…

761
00:57:28,508 --> 00:57:29,759
I ended up like this.

762
00:57:43,565 --> 00:57:44,732
You won't die.

763
00:58:09,132 --> 00:58:10,341
Hello!

764
00:58:10,425 --> 00:58:12,218
Hello to you all!

765
00:58:12,719 --> 00:58:15,680
I'm not dying anymore!

766
00:59:37,887 --> 00:59:39,097
Damn it.

767
01:00:03,454 --> 01:00:04,372
Hello?

768
01:00:05,123 --> 01:00:06,040
<i>It's me.</i>

769
01:00:06,124 --> 01:00:08,042
Master? What is it?

770
01:00:10,503 --> 01:00:11,337
Well…

771
01:00:14,966 --> 01:00:16,968
Are you free this Friday?

772
01:00:18,886 --> 01:00:20,763
I won't even ask why.

773
01:00:20,847 --> 01:00:23,558
I shall dedicate my Friday to you, Master.

774
01:00:25,101 --> 01:00:27,854
Yes, well, you don't have to go that far.

775
01:00:29,689 --> 01:00:31,315
Join me for the street clean-up.

776
01:00:34,694 --> 01:00:35,820
I need a team.

777
01:00:35,903 --> 01:00:38,990
Is that right?
Where are you right now, Master?

778
01:00:39,490 --> 01:00:42,410
Stay right where you are.
I'll zoom right over!

779
01:00:52,503 --> 01:00:53,588
Don't tell me…

780
01:00:55,465 --> 01:00:57,091
you just saved a defect.

781
01:01:05,266 --> 01:01:06,100
I did.

782
01:01:19,071 --> 01:01:20,573
Damn it.

783
01:01:21,949 --> 01:01:22,784
HAESEONG CITY HALL

784
01:01:22,867 --> 01:01:24,827
Is this my uniform?

785
01:01:26,162 --> 01:01:28,581
It's not as cool as I thought it would be.

786
01:01:29,332 --> 01:01:31,501
What do you think?
Do I look good in yellow?

787
01:01:31,584 --> 01:01:33,085
Blink once if I do.

788
01:01:37,590 --> 01:01:38,716
You shouldn't touch…

789
01:01:38,800 --> 01:01:39,675
Fascinating.

790
01:01:39,759 --> 01:01:41,302
Right, lunch.

791
01:01:41,385 --> 01:01:42,887
Lunch is important, isn't it?

792
01:01:42,970 --> 01:01:44,430
The food here is free, right?

793
01:01:44,514 --> 01:01:47,642
To think I'll be dining at City Hall!

794
01:01:48,184 --> 01:01:51,521
But I heard the food here sucks.
What food do you like, Master?

795
01:01:51,604 --> 01:01:53,022
Tell me everything you like.

796
01:01:53,105 --> 01:01:55,066
I won't make it for you, but Grandma will.

797
01:01:56,651 --> 01:01:59,487
I'm the granddaughter of Hearty House,

798
01:01:59,570 --> 01:02:02,031
Eun Chae-ni!

799
01:02:03,908 --> 01:02:06,994
Hey, there's a massage stick here!

800
01:02:07,078 --> 01:02:08,996
I'm sure you all have stiff shoulders.

801
01:02:09,080 --> 01:02:10,081
Is this your desk?

802
01:02:27,640 --> 01:02:29,392
Eunie, where the heck are you?

803
01:02:30,434 --> 01:02:33,062
Ignoring my calls all day!
Are you itching for a fight?

804
01:02:33,646 --> 01:02:35,481
I've been busy. Sorry.

805
01:02:35,565 --> 01:02:37,233
It's nothing major,

806
01:02:37,900 --> 01:02:39,944
but I landed a job at City Hall.

807
01:02:41,320 --> 01:02:42,530
What nonsense is that?

808
01:02:42,613 --> 01:02:43,990
Hold on a second.

809
01:02:44,073 --> 01:02:44,991
Master, come here.

810
01:02:45,074 --> 01:02:48,160
-<i>Get over here. It's urgent.</i>
-Who's she calling Master?

811
01:02:48,244 --> 01:02:50,329
Tell my grandma that I got a job.

812
01:02:50,413 --> 01:02:51,247
-But--
-Hurry.

813
01:02:51,330 --> 01:02:53,499
A job! Tell her I got a job.

814
01:02:54,000 --> 01:02:55,585
Yes, hello.

815
01:02:55,668 --> 01:02:58,170
I'm Lee Un-jeong
of the Civil Complaints Office

816
01:02:58,254 --> 01:02:59,505
at Haeseong City Hall.

817
01:03:00,172 --> 01:03:01,090
Why, of course!

818
01:03:01,591 --> 01:03:03,676
You have my full blessing!

819
01:03:03,759 --> 01:03:04,635
Pardon? Oh, I…

820
01:03:05,136 --> 01:03:06,512
That's not it.

821
01:03:06,596 --> 01:03:10,349
Although it's a temporary position,
Ms. Eun Chae-ni did get a job here.

822
01:03:10,433 --> 01:03:11,434
I'm just confirming…

823
01:03:12,143 --> 01:03:14,729
<i>-Tell her more.</i>
-So, my Chae-ni really…

824
01:03:14,812 --> 01:03:17,815
<i>-That's all you have to say?</i>
-She really found a job at City Hall?

825
01:03:17,899 --> 01:03:19,775
What more should I say? You talk to her.

826
01:03:19,859 --> 01:03:23,571
Grandma, I'm officially on duty,
so I'm really busy. I'll call you later.

827
01:03:23,654 --> 01:03:25,072
My Eunie is really

828
01:03:25,573 --> 01:03:27,533
on the government's payroll?

829
01:03:35,583 --> 01:03:36,417
Hello.

830
01:03:37,710 --> 01:03:38,544
Hello.

831
01:03:39,045 --> 01:03:40,004
Hello…

832
01:03:40,504 --> 01:03:42,465
Hello there. Hello.

833
01:03:42,548 --> 01:03:45,301
No wonder Eunie's fortune
mentioned a government career!

834
01:03:45,384 --> 01:03:47,386
Why, hello there. Hello to you too.

835
01:03:47,470 --> 01:03:49,305
Hello! And hello to you too!

836
01:03:49,388 --> 01:03:52,975
My granddaughter got a job!

837
01:03:53,059 --> 01:03:54,852
Hello. Hello there!

838
01:03:54,936 --> 01:03:57,021
Goodness me!

839
01:03:57,104 --> 01:03:58,981
Why, hello there!

840
01:03:59,065 --> 01:04:00,816
Hello! Hello to you all!

841
01:04:01,317 --> 01:04:03,653
I'm telling you, she got a job!

842
01:04:03,736 --> 01:04:07,198
HEARTY HOUSE

843
01:04:07,281 --> 01:04:09,742
Guys! Ha-na, Du-na, Won-ju, Sang-ju!

844
01:04:09,825 --> 01:04:12,703
Put the rice cake pot on the stove.
It's a family celebration!

845
01:04:13,204 --> 01:04:16,707
Our Chae-ni is going to work
for the government!

846
01:04:20,169 --> 01:04:22,797
Why are you all just standing there?

847
01:04:22,880 --> 01:04:25,216
Go soak the rice, okay?

848
01:04:25,299 --> 01:04:27,885
You have guests.

849
01:04:49,281 --> 01:04:50,825
You haven't changed one bit,

850
01:04:51,325 --> 01:04:52,159
Madam King.

851
01:04:53,995 --> 01:04:55,705
Won-ju, close the store.

852
01:08:30,085 --> 01:08:35,090
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

